What Is Hot‑Start PCR Master Mix?
Hot‑start PCR Master Mix is a ready‑to‑use reagent that simplifies the PCR workflow for both research and clinical laboratories. By incorporating a hot‑start mechanism-either antibody‑masked polymerase, chemical modification, or a hybrid approach-the mix keeps the polymerase inactive at room temperature, eliminating primer‑dimer formation and background amplification. When the reaction reaches the high‑temperature activation step, the enzyme becomes active, delivering highly specific amplification across a wide range of template complexities.

