Key Market Drivers
1. Growing Adoption of Next‑Generation Sequencing (NGS) Platforms
Laboratories worldwide are transitioning to NGS workflows that demand highly specific, contamination‑free amplification for library preparation. Hot‑start chemistries reduce off‑target products, improve read quality and lower the cost per genome, thereby accelerating the uptake of NGS‑based research and diagnostic services.

2. Expansion of Molecular Diagnostic Applications
The surge in infectious‑disease testing, oncology biomarker quantification, and pharmacogenomics has created a steady demand for reliable PCR reagents. Hot‑start mixes deliver the consistency required for point‑of‑care diagnostics, high‑throughput clinical labs, and centralized testing facilities.

